	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64605633"><p>You jest, but it works.  Plenty of people are strongly influenced by apparent popularity, and having far more signs out than another candidate is going to shift some votes.  Or from the other perspective, having far fewer signs than an opponent can discourage people from voting because they don't want to vote for a losing team.</p><p>It's the same kind of herd mentality that results in a small number of extremely popular kids in high school.  We're just wired for it.</p></div>
	</div>

